Note: This is a binary Excel file. The create_file tool expects plain text. I'll provide a CSV template instead that Excel can open directly.

**Excel Import Format for Users:**

**Required Headers (Row 1):**
| name | username | email | password | role |
|------|----------|-------|----------|------|

**Sample Data (Row 2+):**
| John Doe | johndoe | john@example.com | password123 | student |
| Jane Smith | janesmith | jane@example.com | pass456 | admin |
| Student 1 | student1 | s1@school.com | 123456 | student |

**Instructions:**
1. Create new Excel file
2. Row 1: Exactly these headers (case-sensitive)
3. Fill data from Row 2
4. `role`: "student" or "admin" only
5. Save as `.xlsx`
6. Upload via admin/users import form

**Quick CSV Template (save as .csv, open in Excel):**
```
name,username,email,password,role
John Doe,johndoe,john@example.com,password123,student
Jane Smith,janesmith,jane@example.com,pass456,admin
```

Copy-paste ready! 📋
    